==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)pend-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|spenden}}, from {{inh|en|ang|spendan}} (attested especially in compounds {{m|ang|āspendan||to spend}}, {{m|ang|forspendan||to use up, consume}}), from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*spendōn|t=to spend}}, borrowed from {{der|en|la|expendere||to weigh out}}. {{doublet|en|expend}}. Cognate with {{cog|goh|spentōn||to consume, use, spend}} (whence {{cog|de|spenden||to donate, provide}}), {{cog|dum|-}} {{m|nl|spenden||to spend, dedicate}}, Old {{cog|is|spenna||to spend}}.

